        <mxCell id="X7IiD8_YLW-4jLTO91UR-43" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="NOTE: A fully connected graph of this type would contain NxNxM links between chromosomes. This would result in a massive number of N^M potential paths from the first time period to the last. The goal and hope of the second stage of this would be to eliminate a large number of these paths by recognizing ramping constraint violations and only defining links that do not violate these ramping constraints.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For example, on the left we can see that there are no links between chromosome 2 and any chromosomes from the second time period. This immediately reduces the number of potential paths from N^M to (N-1)^M&amp;nbsp;" vertex="1">
